   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="distribution">
      <p>
Distribution
</p>
      <p>
AT, BE, 
CH
, CZ, DE, DK-DEN, GB-GRB, NL, NO-NOR, PL, SE.
</p>
   </tp:treatment-sec>
   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="description">
      <p>
Habitat
</p>
      <p>
Broad-leaved forest, e.g., 
<tp:taxon-name>
Fagus
</tp:taxon-name>
, 
<tp:taxon-name>
Fraxinus
</tp:taxon-name>
, orchards, shrubland, grassland, gardens, occasionally coniferous forests. From 
400–480 m
a.s.l. in 
Switzerland
. Most finds are from synanthropic sites.
</p>
   </tp:treatment-sec>
   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
      <p>
Remarks
</p>
      <p>
Probably introduced to the northern part of its distribution area. 
Tajovský (1996)
described the life cycle of 
<tp:taxon-name>
M. voigti
</tp:taxon-name>
in a suburban forest in 
South Bohemia
.
</p>
